					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-8986880#post-4068654</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-8986880/scp-3709#post-4068654</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Mon, 26 Nov 2018 21:59:33 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Shaggydredlocks</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1722371</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>The object's effects are mildly interesting (or at least, how the one incident plays out is) for what's at its heart a standard item with an OTT anomalous effect directly relating to its function.</p> <p>I could do without the terrible bore of the phone call logs, which don't amount to much, and are very much a retread of 4988. I'm hoping if people continue to write this goi, they can at least offer a bit of diversity.</p> <p>The final reveal, while neatly incorporating the anomaly for some creep, doesn't offer anything fresh. It's weaksauce <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-2535">SCP-2535</a>; hitting on all the basic tropes of spoopy anomalous business, but without anything truly original and outstanding. There's not much I can care about or want to come back to, it just reminds me of other things I'd rather read.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
